name: Web Summit
details: Web Summit is an annual technology conference held in Lisbon, Portugal, considered one of the largest tech events in the world.

name: CES (Consumer Electronics Show)
details: CES is an annual trade show organized by the Consumer Technology Association. It showcases the latest innovations in consumer electronics and technology.

name: Mobile World Congress
details: Mobile World Congress is the largest mobile event in the world, bringing together the latest innovations and leading-edge technology from over 2,400 leading companies.

name: Google I/O
details: Google I/O is an annual developer conference held by Google. It showcases the latest in technology and product innovation from Google.

name: Microsoft Build
details: Microsoft Build is an annual conference event held by Microsoft, aimed at software engineers and web developers.

name: AWS re:Invent
details: AWS re:Invent is an annual learning conference hosted by Amazon Web Services for the global cloud computing community.

name: TechCrunch Disrupt
details: TechCrunch Disrupt is an annual conference hosted by TechCrunch, featuring the latest in technology and startup innovation.

name: Collision
details: Collision is a tech conference produced by the team behind Web Summit. It brings together the people and companies redefining the global tech industry.

name: IFA (Internationale Funkausstellung Berlin)
details: IFA is the world's leading trade show for consumer electronics and home appliances, held annually in Berlin, Germany.

name: GITEX Technology Week
details: GITEX Technology Week is an annual tech event held in Dubai, United Arab Emirates, showcasing the latest trends and innovations across various sectors.
